😎I'LL BE BACK😎⠀
.⠀
👋🏻Hello, Instagram friends!👋🏻⠀
Well, last week week was kinda crazy: on our way to Charleston airport we were rear ended. Me and my mom were seating behind and got injured. Hospitals, insurance companies, flights - it was just insane. But it's all ok now and I am back, grateful for the life I have😔🙏🏼⠀
.⠀
Anyways, let’s talk about something pleasant 🤗The week before the marathon I was in a fantastic holiday prize gifting with other awesome bloggers!⠀
.⠀
🤩So, since there are a lot of new people, I want to welcome all of you to my blog and to tell you a little bit about myself.⠀
.⠀
🥰My name is Maria, I live in Cincinnati since March 2019. I immigrated from Russia because... of my husband: he is American and we were tired to be all the time on the plane so we decided that one of us had to make a move and that was me. I left everything: an awesome job (I was a TV-reporter/tv-presenter + I tv-hosted some great international events like FIFA World Cup 2018), my family and my country to follow my heart. And here I am!💃🏼⠀
.⠀
✅Now in Cincinnati I'm getting ready to become a real-estate agent/investor and to work with one of the greatest brokerages in the world! I haven't abandoned my artistic nature and in this moment I am represented by NV Talent agency which every now and then sends me to some great castings.⠀
.⠀
📖Here in my blog I write mostly about everything: beautiful places, good food, some beauty stuff and my observations about life in the US🇺🇸⠀
.⠀
🤗Welcome and let’s be friends!❤️⠀
.⠀
👋🏻ВЕРНУТЬСЯ ОТТУДА?..👋🏻⠀
.⠀
👉🏼Ставь лайк мне за старания👈🏼⠀
.⠀
Звучит страшно, да? Не буду долго вас томить и посвящать в ненужные подробности. Просто скажу одно: цените вашу жизнь и близких. Одна секунда, один пропущенный поворот может многое изменить😔⠀
.⠀
✅И еще: всегда покупайте страховку для путешествующих - если что-то произойдет, она себя окупить в сотни раз.⠀
.⠀
❤️На фото - я счастливая в Чикаго в декабре! Эта скульптура в простонародье называется "бобик", хотя сам скульптор назвал ее более романтично "Облачные ворота". Один из самых узнаваемых символов холодного Чикаго❤️

According to my Uber driver, it was a 3.5 minute ambitious visit to the bean hoping there is no sun, and tourist crowd in the middle of the day. Anish Kapoor’s Cloud Gate, in its winter glory (OK-OK, glory happened two nights ago!) There is nothing more I wanted for “self” on this sleepless, busy and tiring work trip. Is cloud gate the ultimate within-without nirvana? Selflessly reflect the mood around while being selfishly superficial?

The Cloud Gate o llamado popularmente “The Bean” es una escultura del artista Anish Kapoor que corresponde al movimiento artístico biomorfismo, el cual está basado en formas orgánicas de la naturaleza. 🌿 Su reflejo y forma están inspirados en la apariencia del mercurio líquido y en la superficie se reflejan las nubes y los rascacielos del entorno ☁️🏙 haciendo que sea un bello espectáculo. Aunque pareciera que es 1 sola pieza, en realidad está compuesto de 168 placas de acero inoxidable. 😱

Está escultura se ha convertido en todo un icono de Chicago. Déjanos muchas ☁️☁️☁️ si te gustaría visitar la Ciudad de los Vientos y tomarte una foto aquí. 😍 .

WHAT TO DO & EAT IN CHICAGO {save this 📌 & share with your friends}⁣
⁣
One of the best cities in 🇺🇸 no debate necessary. These are the things you MUST cross off your list 📝 when you’re there!⁣
⁣
✔️ @skydeckchicago (pictured) : Catch the best bird’s-eye view of the city (if anyone tells you otherwise they’re lying) & if you’re fearless get your picture sitting on top of the famous glass box 😰 — Don’t forget to check the weather BEFORE purchasing your tickets online because you may be signing up on a day where there’s zero visibility & they WILL take your 💰 knowing you won’t see a thing when you get up (it’s happened to me 😩)⁣
⁣
✔️ CloudGate aka “The Bean” : Get there early or you’ll be forced to photoshop all the intruders out of your pictures 😅 ( you didn’t go to Chicago if you don’t go here 🤷🏾‍♀️) ⁣
⁣
✔️ Try deep-dish 🍕 @pequodspizza .Thick, carmalized, with a thin layer of cheese along the outer crust. Rated # 4️⃣ out of 101 best pizza’s in the country!⁣
⁣
✔️ Visit a Rooftop Bar 👇🏾 (3 of the best!)⁣
➖ @lhchicago⁣
➖ @cindysrooftop⁣
➖ @abarestaurant⁣
⁣
✔️ Sushi 🍣 Lover? Some of the best sushi I’ve ever had is served @therealsushisan ! Definitely order the Tako Taco as an appetizer (you might order a 2nd because it’s soooo good!)⁣
⁣
✔️ Do breakfast the right way @batterandberries and berries. Serving over 50 different variations of French toast 😱. Best Brunch spot period. Google it.⁣
⁣
✔️ Visit Lincoln Park where you’ll find the honeycomb structure that’s the perfect photo op.⁣
—⁣
Chicago is my favorite because it’s full of outdoor activities & diverse in food (my love language). Headed to Chicago? What’s first on your to-do list ?

Cloud Gate aka The Bean 
Sooo many tourists, it’s super crowdy. One guy trying to take a photo, was walking backwards and bumped into me almost knocking me down (I was sideways so I didn’t see him). When traveling, these crowds sometimes irritates me, but it’s unavoidable as I’m a part of this crowd 😜 
I like to learn and play with reflection in photography. It took me a while to take a photo with kind of tourist chaos but I think it was worth it 😄
___________________________________________________________
Cloud Gate aka The Bean (Fasolka)
Bardzo dużo turystów, jest super tłoczno.  Jeden facet próbujący zrobić zdjęcie, szedł do tyłu i wpadł na mnie prawie przewracając mnie (siedziałam bokiem, więc go nie widziałam). Podczas podróżowania czasami drażnią mnie te tłumy, ale jest to nieuniknione, bo sama jestem częścią tego tłumu 😜 
Lubie się uczyć zabawy z odbiciem w fotografii. Trochę zajęło mi zrobienie zdjęcia z turystycznym chaosem, ale myślę, że było warto 😄

The Bean (Cloud Gate) - "The Bean" is one of the Chicago's most popular sites. The sculpture which is in bean shaped is officially titled "Cloud Gate" is one of the world's largest permanent outdoor art installation.
.
It was unveiled in 2004. The Bean's reflective surface was inspired by liquid Mercury and also invites visitors to touch the surface and observe their own reflection. The shiny exterior reflects the people moving around the park.
.
This Bean is made of stainless steel massive plates. It was designed by Indian-born British sculptor Anish Kapoor.
.

Quando sono in una città nuova non amo molto prendere la metro, perché credo che poi ti perdi qualcosa. E se anche non hai molto tempo e non sei un turista ma stai lavorando, c’è sempre qualcosa da scoprire! #cloudgate è una scultura pubblica dell'artista britannico di origini indiane Anish Kapoor e si trova al centro della AT&T Plaza nel Millennium Park a Chicago, Illinois, USA. La scultura e la AT&T Plaza si trovano tra il "Park Grill" ed il "Jay Pritzker Pavilion". Costruito tra il 2004 ed il 2006, la scultura è soprannominata "The Bean" (in italiano "Il Fagiolo") per via della sua forma. Fatto di 168 lastre di acciaio inossidabile saldate insieme, la sua lucidissima superficie esteriore non ha saldature visibili; le sue dimensioni sono 10 m × 20 m × 13 m e pesa circa 100 tonnellate.

L’opera è più conosciuta come The Bean, il fagiolo.Ma essa è un arco, alto circa 3.5 metri, rappresenta anche una porta d’accesso alla città, un gate appunto.Perché la forza del Cloud Gate è proprio il suo rapporto con la città e con il cielo. Infatti, questa forma di acciaio tirato a specchio lunga oltre 20 metri e alta più di 10 riflette tanto lo skyline di Chicago che le nuvole. L’opera muta il suo aspetto a seconda del lato da cui la si guardi e delle condizioni del cielo.

Cloud Gate is a public sculpture by Indian-born British artist Sir Anish Kapoor, that is the centerpiece of AT&T Plaza at Millennium Park in the Loop community area of Chicago, Illinois. The sculpture and AT&T Plaza are located on top of Park Grill, between the Chase Promenade and McCormick Tribune Plaza & Ice Rink. Constructed between 2004 and 2006, the sculpture is nicknamed The Bean because of its shape, a name Kapoor initially disliked, but later grew fond of. Made up of 168 stainless steel plates welded together, its highly polished exterior has no visible seams. It measures 33 by 66 by 42 feet (10 by 20 by 13 m), and weighs 110 short tons (100 t; 98 long tons). https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cloud_Gate .

CHICAGO, IL - As he entered Millenium Park, Naperville North High School senior Kenny Sanders could not help but fantasize about graduating from a midwestern state school with a finance degree, moving to Chicago, and spending every waking moment of his free time hanging out at the Bean.
.
“I can’t believe people live here and get to hangout at the coolest places Chicago has to offer, like the Water Tower, the Ferris Wheel at Navy Pier, and the Riverwalk. They can eat lunch everyday at FoodLife!” Sanders said. “But I’m immediately going to hangout at The Bean every single day once I move down here and live right next to the Willis Tower.” Sanders would have daydreams about his selfies The Bean and getting drenched by the water fountains of spitting people.
.
“I’m going to spend hours at The Bean and put my fingers on it and say, ‘I’m flicking The Bean, no one else has thought of this before,’ and it’ll be great,” Sanders said. “Thankfully I’m in 20 AP classes so I’ll be able to graduate college in three years, which means I’ll get to move to Chicago even quicker.” .
Sources last saw Sanders purchasing a Chicago flag for his dorm room at a Michigan Avenue tourist shop.

Você já conhece aquela técnica de sentir com o coração quando está com alguma indecisão? 
O coração é muito sábio, e quando tomamos decisões baseadas no nosso coração, por experiência própria, sempre é a melhor escolha!!!
Ta, mas como você faz isso? 
Quando estiver em dúvida entre dois caminhos, pare alguns instante, feche os olhos, respire profundamente e pense em cada opção e sentindo como seria cada uma delas, aquele caminho que te trouxer mais expansão e sensação boa no peito, pode ir sem medo, essa será a boa escolha!!! .
.
Amanhã, a lua entra na sua fase minguante, que deixemos minguar tudo o que precise finalizar. 
Que as limpezas necessárias sejam feitas para que o novo tenha espaço. ✨
Ouça seu coração. Desapegue. Perdoe. Deixe ir. Cure. Limpe. Siga com o coração leve e em paz! 
Super beijo, 
Eliane Mácedo

Chicago is the perfect weekend trip for any food and art enthusiast. The city boasts some of the best restaurants, bars and museums in the US. Besides visiting Anish Kapoor’s iconic Cloud Gate sculpture, be sure to  visit the Art Institute of Chicago, Frank Lloyd Wright’s Home and Studio in Oak Park and The Second City, the legendary stand up comedy club where some of the most iconic comedians on SNL started their careers (check out the Old Town Ale House right next door, where Anthony Bourdain filmed an episode of his CNN show!) Food wise, we highly recommend @parachutechicago in Avondale,  #fatricechicago for Chinese-Portuguese fusion, @girl.and.the.goat for bold flavors and #schwachicago for a highlight experience. A Friday favorite, Chicago! Why do we travel? I have been lucky enough in life to travel for fun and work, feeding my constant sense of wonder and hunger to learn as much as possible (not to mention my love of food, but that's a seperate post 😉). I suppose the immersion factor that comes with travel is a big driver, as well. The world is so big and yet, so small, at the same time. I see these traits in my son, along with a Peter Pan-like sense of adventure that children possess, so I want to show him everything!  These are from a family multi- places-vacation, this past Summer.  We soaked up every precious moment together in this vibrant city with a deep soul. Chicago is an excellent pedestrian city and  offers so many different experiences, from the touristy  architecture sight-seeing river tours, exploring the Navy pier, the required photos by Buckingham fountain and  the " bean", to taking in the magnificent views from the John Hancock tower, as well as visiting locations like Thalia Hall ( the building in Disney's show,  Raven's Home) which has an amazing restaurant below it! (They serve dutch baby pancakes  and beignets! I will weave those into another post at some point) Chicago, we will be back again. 🥰💕

Cloud Gate is a public sculpture by Indian-born British artist Sir Anish Kapoor, that is the centerpiece of AT&T Plaza at Millennium Park in the Loop community area of Chicago, Illinois.

"보이는 것이 다가 아니고 겉으로 나타나는 것이 다 말해주는 것은 아니다"

영상 속 작품은 아니쉬 카푸어(anish kapoor)의 하강(descension)입니다.

물이 소용돌이 치며 심연으로 빨려들어가는 듯한 모습을 연출했죠. 그림이나 비디오아트가 아닌 실제 검은물을 이용해 설치된 작품입니다.

인도에서 태어난 아니쉬 카푸어는 세계에서도 손꼽히는 영국의 대표적인 조각가입니다.

현대예술이 난해해서 다가가기 힘들었다면, 그의 작품은 주로 관람객들이 직접 보고 느끼며 체험할 수 있는 기회를 줍니다. 딱딱하고 어렵기만한 예술이 아닌 '내'가 주체가 되는 예술이죠.

보는 이의 관점과 위치, 방향에 따라서 작품은 다르게 보여지고 다르게 해석됩니다.

그래서 그는 자신의 작품을 두고 "보이는 것이 다가 아니다"고 말하는 건지도 모릅니다.

아니쉬 카푸어의 흥미진진한 이야기는 추후에 또 준비해오도록 할게요!

The bean

Kapoor's design was inspired by liquid mercury and the sculpture's surface reflects and distorts the city's skyline. Visitors are able to walk around and under Cloud Gate's high arch. On the underside is the "omphalos" (Greek for "navel"), a concave chamber that warps and multiplies reflections.
This mirror-like surface would reflect the Chicago skyline, but its elliptical shape would distort and twist the reflected image. As visitors walk around the structure, its surface acts like a fun-house mirror as it distorts their reflections.

We spent a couple of days in Chicago on our way from Texas -> Sweden. A couple of things: I didn’t know Chicago was so pretty! I also didn’t know that it is quite lively. I didn’t know that when we were being touristy at Cloudgate (along with the lady carrying a cat around) 😺, that we were just a short walk from Lake Michigan. I didn’t know that, despite sitting by a lake, it has a really dry climate. And...I certainly didn’t know that I might almost lose my life (or a leg) taking a Lyft back from downtown to where we were staying. The Lyft driver felt really bad about it. Oh! And, lastly, I really didn’t know that an airport pickup zone could be as intense as ORD. Seriously, just have your people do a slow roll, because there is zero stopping. 🤩 See you next time, Chicago!

Day 158. 2019. 11. 8. 안녕 시카고👋🏻
⠀
오후 5시반 비행기로 시카고를 떠나는 날. 여전히 춥다🤧 오늘은 거의 쇼핑만 했다. 우리는 지금껏 고프로 대신 방수카메라를 쓰고 있었는데, 스노클링 할 땐 너무 좋지만 스쿠버를 할 땐 쓸수가 없어 아쉬웠었다. 다합에서 괜찮은 고프로 중고 매물을 놓친 이후에 곧 고프로 8이 나오니 멕시코 가기 전에 사야겠다 마음 먹었었는데, 오늘이 그 날 이었다. 어제 타겟에 갔다가 허탕을 치고, 오늘은 베스트 바이를 찾아갔다. 하나 남은 방수하우징도 겨우겨우 찾아서 구매 성공!
⠀
또 시카고와 큰 상관은 없지만 오며가며 지나다녔던 디즈니스토어를 찾아갔다. 한국에서 잘 못보는 류의 디즈니 인형을 사기 위해서👀 오리 삼형제 휴이듀이루이 인형을 사고 싶어서 간건데, 막상 가보니 더 이상 재고가 없다고 했다😱 한참을 고민하다가 아쉬운 마음에 도널드덕과 데이지를 샀다. (지나고 나서 생각해보니 아프리카 여행도 반쯤 기념할 겸 아기 심바와 아기 날라를 살 걸 그랬다 싶다.)
⠀
공항 갈 시간을 생각하면 시간이 빠듯한 와중에 가구 쇼룸과 브런치 카페가 함께 있는 3 arts club cafe를 가보고 싶었다! 버스를 타고도 한참을 걸어야해서 추위를 버텨가며 겨우겨우 도착했는데 웨이팅 2시간😂 어차피 비행기 시간때문에 당장 들어가도 음료만 먹고 나와야 할 시간이었는데, 아쉽지만 차라리 잘됐다 하면서 발걸음을 돌렸다.
⠀

A break during Backstage 2020, allowed me to make a quick visit at The Bean, which is just a block away from my hotel. 
Being at The Bean and seeing only very few people (There's always a big crowd at the place) were there at that moment, was a very pleasant surprise to me. Thank God. Perhaps since the Lord knows that for a long time now I've wanted to go there and get a photo of me being there...He was like "There you go, it's all to yourself. Enjoy!" The Cloud Gate also known as The Bean, is a world famous public sculpture by Indian-born British artist Sir Anish Kapoor, located at The Millennium Park in Chicago, Illinois. 
The sculpture, which was constructed in 2006, is nicknamed The Bean because of its shape. It is made up of 168 stainless steel plates welded together. It measures 33 by 66 by 42 feet and weighs 110 tons.

Kapoor's design was inspired by liquid mercury as its surface reflects and distorts the city's skyline. Visitors are able to walk around and under its 12-foot high arch.

The sculpture builds upon many of Kapoor's artistic themes. It is popular with tourists in the Windy City as a photo-taking opportunity for its unique reflective properties.

Auch wenn ich nur einen kurzen Aufenthalt in Chicago hatte, konnte ich dennoch zum Cloud Gate gehen. Chicago ist eine der größten Städte in den USA 🇺🇸 und liegt am Lake Michigan in Illinois. Das Cloud Gate ist eine öffentliche Skulptur des indisch-britischen Künstlers Anish Kapoor. Es steht im Millennium Park von Chicago, Illinois. Zwischen 2004 und 2006 wurde sie erstellt und wird aufgrund ihrer Form, die an eine Bohne erinnert auch The Bean genannt. Zusammengeschweißt aus 168 Edelstahlplatten hat sie keine sichtbaren Nähte und ist hochglanzpoliert. Es sieht cool aus und ein Foto davor zu schießen ist zwar sehr cool aber durch all die Besucher nicht immer einfach. Man sollte schon früh Morgens dahin, wenn man große Ansammlungen von Menschen auf seinen Fotos vermeiden möchte 😅 
Gibt es welche unter euch, die es geschafft haben ganz alleine auf dem Foto zu sein? 
Ich habe es dieses mal nicht geschafft aber vielleicht beim nächsten mal 😜 .

The sculpture is a popular tourist attraction thanks to its reflective properties that make for a great photo-op.

✅Cloud Gate is a public sculpture by Indian-born British artist Sir Anish Kapoor, that is the centerpiece of AT&T Plaza at Millennium Park in the Loop community area of Chicago. 👷🏽‍♂️Constructed between 2004 and 2006, the sculpture is nicknamed The Bean because of its shape, a name Kapoor initially disliked, but later grew fond of. Made up of 168 stainless steel plates welded together, its highly polished exterior has no visible seams✨
